The African National Congress (ANC) and South African Communist Party (SACP) are holding a virtual ceremony to commemorate what would have been a struggle icon, Harry Gwala’s one-hundredth birthday.  ANC president Cyril Ramaphosa addresses the virtual celebration. For more, click the video link below:   @MYANC President Cyril Ramaphosa, will today, 30 July 2020, address a virtual centenary celebration in honour of Isithwalandwe/Seaparankoe Comrade Harry Gwala. Born on the 30 July 1920 near Pietermaritzburg, Cde Gwala also became known as Munt’omdala – the Lion of the Midlands. pic.twitter.com/8tfmv28kus — African National Congress (@MYANC) July 30, 2020 <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span>